It's Rosemary.

461
00:21:26,986 --> 00:21:29,086
Are you sick, babe?

462
00:21:29,088 --> 00:21:32,790
[ Pensee ]
Oh, Rosemary. Oh, my God.
I think that maybe I--

463
00:21:32,792 --> 00:21:34,592
Yvette.
I'm out here too.

464
00:21:34,594 --> 00:21:37,428
Hi, Yvette.
Hi.

465
00:21:37,430 --> 00:21:39,463
Let me come in--
No, no, no, no, no.

466
00:21:39,465 --> 00:21:42,066
You don't need anything,
do you?

467
00:21:42,068 --> 00:21:45,436
- You'll be better in time
for the photos, right?
- Uh--

468
00:21:45,438 --> 00:21:48,739
Pensee? You just stay
in there like a good girl.

469
00:21:48,741 --> 00:21:52,310
You drink lots of water.
You do not let anyone
in the room.

470
00:21:52,312 --> 00:21:55,413
You don't want anyone
to see the way your--

471
00:21:56,515 --> 00:21:58,649
uh, your condition
is looking.

472
00:21:58,651 --> 00:22:00,251
[ Chuckles ]
Okay?

473
00:22:01,153 --> 00:22:02,453
Okay.

474
00:22:02,455 --> 00:22:05,523
Love you, dear.
Okay.

475
00:22:05,525 --> 00:22:07,825
Okay.
Yeah. You're fine.

476
00:22:07,827 --> 00:22:09,226
Don't worry about her.
She is going to be fine.

477
00:22:10,595 --> 00:22:13,798
Hey, everyone out there
in Pensee land.

478
00:22:13,800 --> 00:22:16,934
Like a goof, I got hurt
at the wedding weekend.

479
00:22:16,936 --> 00:22:20,171
I don't want to make a scene
or do anything stupid, so,

480
00:22:20,173 --> 00:22:23,441
I'm gonna sneak out the window
and run through the woods
to the highway...

481
00:22:23,443 --> 00:22:25,509
and then take a taxi
to the hospital.

482
00:22:25,511 --> 00:22:28,145
And I'm bringing you all
along with me, guys.

483
00:22:28,147 --> 00:22:29,847
Wish me luck!

484
00:22:29,849 --> 00:22:31,782
[ Kisses ]

485
00:22:31,784 --> 00:22:34,885
[ Sighs ]
You know. It's, uh--

486
00:22:34,887 --> 00:22:38,489
Everything happens for
a reason, even accidents.

487
00:22:38,491 --> 00:22:41,025
There's a thing
called happy accidents,
you know?

488
00:22:41,027 --> 00:22:45,429
It's possible all life
on Earth began
by accident.

489
00:23:02,514 --> 00:23:03,714
Pensee?

490
00:23:04,916 --> 00:23:05,750
Pensee?

491
00:23:07,853 --> 00:23:09,720
This is harder
than I expected.

492
00:23:10,889 --> 00:23:12,890
Oh. Uh--
[ Dishes Clatter ]

493
00:23:12,892 --> 00:23:14,925
[ Kicks Door ]
Ow.

494
00:23:16,695 --> 00:23:17,962
[ Groans ]
Oh, God.

495
00:23:21,266 --> 00:23:22,533
Okay.

496
00:23:22,535 --> 00:23:24,602
But I'm sticking to it,
guys.

497
00:23:24,604 --> 00:23:28,105
You gotta believe in yourself
and find your greatness, right?

498
00:23:28,107 --> 00:23:31,108
Pensee? Pensee!

499
00:23:31,110 --> 00:23:32,743
What on earth
are you doing?

500
00:23:32,745 --> 00:23:34,712
Don't worry.
No one will see.

501
00:23:34,714 --> 00:23:36,614
It's broad daylight!

502
00:23:36,616 --> 00:23:40,184
You come back in here
right now, young lady.
You will ruin everything!

503
00:23:40,186 --> 00:23:41,619
Come in.
No, no.

504
00:23:41,621 --> 00:23:43,888
You come in right now.
Don't pull on it.
Don't you dare.

505
00:23:43,890 --> 00:23:45,956
Come in!
You're the devil
and you know it!

506
00:23:45,958 --> 00:23:47,958
[ Yvette ]
It's my wedding,
and you won't ruin it!

507
00:23:47,960 --> 00:23:50,394
[ Pensee ] It's not
your wedding. It's Robert
and Rosemary's wedding.

508
00:23:50,396 --> 00:23:52,430
[ Yvette ]
Fine! But you're ruining it!

509
00:23:52,432 --> 00:23:54,632
Stop! You're gonna
make me fall!

510
00:23:54,634 --> 00:23:56,600
[ Yelps, Screams ]

511
00:23:58,970 --> 00:24:00,404
[ Yvette ]
Pensee?
[ Groans ]

512
00:24:00,406 --> 00:24:02,540
Oh. You don't want
to go in there.

513
00:24:02,542 --> 00:24:03,707
I have to get
some Pepto.

514
00:24:08,113 --> 00:24:13,117
♪ [ Pop ]

515
00:24:15,153 --> 00:24:17,321
[ Yvette ]
Ted! Ted!

516
00:24:19,825 --> 00:24:21,292
Could you come with me
for a moment, please?

517
00:24:21,294 --> 00:24:23,194
Can you just let me
eat this Danish, please?

518
00:24:24,963 --> 00:24:27,465
This is an emergency.
Mm-hmm.

519
00:24:27,467 --> 00:24:30,668
It's about Pensee's, uh--

520
00:24:30,670 --> 00:24:31,802
diarrhea.
Oh.

521
00:24:31,804 --> 00:24:34,171
It's gotten very messy.
Okay, okay, okay.

522
00:24:34,173 --> 00:24:36,173
Okay, okay.
Let's go. Let's go.
Let's go.

523
00:24:40,812 --> 00:24:42,746
Hurry up.

524
00:24:42,748 --> 00:24:44,348
Oh, my God!
[ Groans ]

525
00:24:44,350 --> 00:24:46,050
Oh, man up, Ted!

526
00:24:50,922 --> 00:24:52,990
Oh. Mmm.
Breathe in, breathe out.

527
00:24:52,992 --> 00:24:54,692
I'll get you a paper bag
in a second.

528
00:24:54,694 --> 00:24:56,460
[ Woman ]
The one thing
I didn't understand...

529
00:24:56,462 --> 00:24:59,697
is that you're
at a wedding this weekend--
Babe. Babe. Stop talking.

530
00:24:59,699 --> 00:25:02,633
Stop. Listen to
what I am saying, okay?

531
00:25:02,635 --> 00:25:04,869
I got this fuckin' thing
on my lip.

532
00:25:04,871 --> 00:25:06,804
I don't know what it is.

533
00:25:06,806 --> 00:25:09,707
Go to the computer,
fire up WebMed.

534
00:25:09,709 --> 00:25:12,843
Just-- I'm gonna
shoot the thing on my lip...

535
00:25:12,845 --> 00:25:15,145
and I'm gonna play it back
so I can describe it to you.

536
00:25:15,147 --> 00:25:18,048
I don't know what it is,
and that affects both of us.

537
00:25:18,050 --> 00:25:21,151
Yeah. Yeah.
That's the point, retard.
Thank you.

538
00:25:21,153 --> 00:25:23,020
I don't care about
this thing on your lip.
I'm trying--

539
00:25:23,022 --> 00:25:25,189
Fucking ridiculous.

540
00:25:25,191 --> 00:25:26,891
[ Ted ]
Should we call a doctor?

541
00:25:26,893 --> 00:25:28,359
[ Yvette ]
She's dead.
She can't get any deader.

542
00:25:28,361 --> 00:25:30,060
Should we bury her?

543
00:25:30,062 --> 00:25:32,229
There's no time
for that, Ted.

544
00:25:32,231 --> 00:25:35,666
Besides, Pensee would have
wanted us to just
hide her corpse.

545
00:25:35,668 --> 00:25:38,502
[ Ted ]
What about that?
Ooh, that's good thinking.

546
00:25:38,504 --> 00:25:39,870
[ Grunts ]

547
00:25:40,972 --> 00:25:42,973
[ Yvette Grunts ]

548
00:25:47,646 --> 00:25:49,647
[ Ted ]
Okay. Okay.

549
00:25:49,649 --> 00:25:51,549
Oh, my God.
That is fucked up.

550
00:25:51,551 --> 00:25:54,118
[ Ted Muttering ]

551
00:25:55,554 --> 00:25:59,089
Get her arm--
Hold on.

552
00:25:59,091 --> 00:26:00,891
Here. Hold on.
Do you have any lotion?

553
00:26:00,893 --> 00:26:02,593
Maybe we could, like,
grease her up.

554
00:26:02,595 --> 00:26:05,095
We'll just cram it down
with the lid.
Just cram the lid down.

555
00:26:05,097 --> 00:26:06,564
I don't-- Oh.

556
00:26:06,566 --> 00:26:08,866
[ Blaze ]
Are they-- Oh, sh--
Is that the cameraman?

557
00:26:08,868 --> 00:26:11,669
Um, excuse me.

558
00:26:11,671 --> 00:26:16,073
Mr. Cameraman?
This isn't what--

559
00:26:16,075 --> 00:26:17,942
Could we talk to you
for a second?

560
00:26:17,944 --> 00:26:20,010
- Grab that rock!
- This rock right here?

561
00:26:20,012 --> 00:26:21,745
What the fuck
are you doing?
No, that rock!

562
00:26:21,747 --> 00:26:23,213
Dude, I'm just high.
I just imagined--

563
00:26:23,215 --> 00:26:25,082
What-- What are you doing?
You fucking--

564
00:26:25,084 --> 00:26:26,550
- [ Blow Lands ]
- Don't run from me.
Stop it!

565
00:26:26,552 --> 00:26:28,218
Come on, man! I'll give you
back the money, dude!

566
00:26:28,220 --> 00:26:31,355
- [ Blaze Groaning ]
- [ Yvette ]
Get his head.

567
00:26:31,357 --> 00:26:32,556
No. Oh, shit!

568
00:26:32,558 --> 00:26:35,059
- [ Blow Lands ]
- [ Groans ]

569
00:26:35,061 --> 00:26:37,027
I think I killed him.
I had to, right?

570
00:26:37,029 --> 00:26:39,530
He could have had a gun.
You think he may
have a gun, right?

571
00:26:39,532 --> 00:26:43,968
He could have had a-- Right?
Y-Yes. Well, always
best to play it safe.

572
00:26:43,970 --> 00:26:47,037
[ Stammers ]
How am I gonna tell my wife
she married someone...

573
00:26:47,039 --> 00:26:49,740
who hit someone in the head
with a rock and then he died?
Ted.

574
00:26:49,742 --> 00:26:52,076
What?
You're not going
to tell your wife.

575
00:26:52,078 --> 00:26:54,545
I tell her everything.
She knows everything.
It's why she doesn't like me.

576
00:26:56,414 --> 00:27:00,618
Here you are.
I was starting to think
you were ignoring me.

577
00:27:00,620 --> 00:27:02,786
What? No, honey.

578
00:27:02,788 --> 00:27:05,055
I'm just--
I was distracted.

579
00:27:05,057 --> 00:27:07,992
My dad's been looking for you.
He said you guys were supposed
to have a man-to-man talk.

580
00:27:07,994 --> 00:27:09,660
Yeah. Yeah.
You said you were into it.

581
00:27:09,662 --> 00:27:11,295
Yeah, I gotta go see him.

582
00:27:12,464 --> 00:27:13,931
You all right, baby?
Yeah. Excuse me.

583
00:27:13,933 --> 00:27:16,266
I gotta talk to my mom
real fast.

584
00:27:16,268 --> 00:27:17,701
See you at
the wedding photos!

585
00:27:19,838 --> 00:27:22,106
Mom? Mom.
Mom, Mom, Mom.

586
00:27:22,108 --> 00:27:24,274
I'm in the middle
of something.
I can see that, Mom.

587
00:27:24,276 --> 00:27:26,944
Why do you have
an ax?

588
00:27:26,946 --> 00:27:28,812
I got it
off one of the gardeners.

589
00:27:28,814 --> 00:27:31,181
Rodrigo has everything.
Oh, yeah?

590
00:27:31,183 --> 00:27:33,450
That doesn't really
answer my question, Mom.

591
00:27:33,452 --> 00:27:38,589
This doesn't have anything
to do with Pensee's, uh,
car trouble?

592
00:27:38,591 --> 00:27:40,024
Um, y--

593
00:27:40,026 --> 00:27:41,492
It died.

594
00:27:44,262 --> 00:27:48,032
Huh? She--
Pensee's car died.

595
00:27:48,034 --> 00:27:52,603
You said--
You said she was--
it was fine, Mom.

596
00:27:52,605 --> 00:27:55,139
Uh, it was.

597
00:27:55,141 --> 00:27:58,842
Then it fell out a window
and died.

598
00:27:58,844 --> 00:28:03,547
Then one of the cameramen--
Mm-hmm?

599
00:28:03,549 --> 00:28:05,549
His car died too.

600
00:28:05,551 --> 00:28:07,217
What are you
talking about, Mom?

601
00:28:07,219 --> 00:28:09,653
His car--
Yeah?

602
00:28:09,655 --> 00:28:12,222
saw Pensee's car--
Uh-huh.

603
00:28:12,224 --> 00:28:16,860
then wanted
to ruin the wedding,
so Ted...

604
00:28:16,862 --> 00:28:19,296
hit it with a rock.

605
00:28:19,298 --> 00:28:22,566
Oh, Robert.
There you are, my boy.
Oh, hey!

606
00:28:22,568 --> 00:28:26,236
Uh-- Don't worry.
Your mother is looking out
for you.

607
00:28:26,238 --> 00:28:28,672
You just keep
enjoying yourself.
Okay.

608
00:28:28,674 --> 00:28:31,575
Where are the cars
now, Ma?

609
00:28:31,577 --> 00:28:33,210
Everything okay?
Yeah.

610
00:28:33,212 --> 00:28:36,246
No, Judge--
Your Honor. Sir.
Everything's great.

611
00:28:36,248 --> 00:28:40,584
I think it's high time that
you learned to call me Flip.
[ Toilet Flushes ]

612
00:28:40,586 --> 00:28:43,087
- Ah. Yes, sir, Flip.
- Whoa.

613
00:28:43,089 --> 00:28:47,324
We are pleased as punch
to welcome you
into the Milton family.

614
00:28:47,326 --> 00:28:50,928
Well, I am honored
to be a part
of your family, sir.

615
00:28:50,930 --> 00:28:54,264
You know what?
Can I just talk to my dad for
one minute, while we're here?

616
00:28:54,266 --> 00:28:56,100
Excuse me real quick.
Hey, Dad?

617
00:28:56,102 --> 00:28:58,368
Mom's, uh--
I need you to watch
out for her, okay?

618
00:28:58,370 --> 00:29:00,037
'Cause she's getting
a little crazy
with her wedding planning.

619
00:29:00,039 --> 00:29:03,907
Robbie. She's always been crazy.

620
00:29:03,909 --> 00:29:06,043
I know that you guys
aren't on good terms
right now, okay?

621
00:29:06,045 --> 00:29:07,845
But I really need you
right now.

622
00:29:07,847 --> 00:29:10,080
Make sure she doesn't
do anything out
of the ordinary, okay?

623
00:29:10,082 --> 00:29:12,950
Yeah. If that's
what you need me to do.
Okay. That's what I need.

624
00:29:12,952 --> 00:29:15,619
[ Milton ]
Uh, Robert? Come on in.
Yeah. Here I come!

625
00:29:15,621 --> 00:29:18,589
- Here I come, Pop!
- Do you know what
they're having for dinner?

626
00:29:18,591 --> 00:29:21,525
[ Robert ] It's kind of weird,
isn't it, having all
these cameras around here?

627
00:29:21,527 --> 00:29:23,761
[ Milton ]
I have an election
coming up in November, Robert.

628
00:29:23,763 --> 00:29:26,930
Charles Beaumont
is really gunning for my seat,

629
00:29:26,932 --> 00:29:28,132
just waiting for me
to slip up.

630
00:29:29,534 --> 00:29:31,101
[ Loud Clang ]

631
00:29:39,911 --> 00:29:42,946
Okeydokey.
Uh, excuse me.

632
00:29:42,948 --> 00:29:45,315
[ Panting ]
[ Yvette ]
Ted?

633
00:29:45,317 --> 00:29:47,951
I got an ax.
No! I don't want
to cut him up!

634
00:29:47,953 --> 00:29:50,287
The key, I find,

635
00:29:50,289 --> 00:29:52,756
is one must live
one's life in private...

636
00:29:52,758 --> 00:29:57,594
just as honorably
and forthrightly
as one does in public.

637
00:29:57,596 --> 00:29:59,062
That makes sense.

638
00:29:59,064 --> 00:30:01,999
Since I do have
an election coming up--

639
00:30:02,001 --> 00:30:03,200
Anything you need
to tell me, Robert?

640
00:30:04,569 --> 00:30:06,570
Any skeletons in the closet?

641
00:30:08,173 --> 00:30:09,206
Your closet?

642
00:30:11,409 --> 00:30:15,813
No. This is man's work,
and this body's too big
to carry around.

643
00:30:15,815 --> 00:30:19,082
Look, we have to make it
look like a Mexican
drug cartel did it.

644
00:30:19,084 --> 00:30:20,584
Isn't that smart?
Come on.

645
00:30:20,586 --> 00:30:22,920
What was that?
Do you hear something?

646
00:30:22,922 --> 00:30:26,456
No. You're just being paranoid.
Come on. Take the ax.
No. Shh.

647
00:30:26,458 --> 00:30:29,326
[ Rhythmic Knocking ]

648
00:30:29,328 --> 00:30:31,094
Oh. Uh--

649
00:30:31,863 --> 00:30:33,630
See-See who it is.

650
00:30:33,632 --> 00:30:36,099
No! I know what that means.

651
00:30:36,101 --> 00:30:39,069
God. I have to do
everything around here.

652
00:30:41,005 --> 00:30:43,173
Shh.

653
00:30:43,175 --> 00:30:45,876
- Oh!
- So this is your room, huh?

654
00:30:45,878 --> 00:30:49,046
Not a good time, Hank.
[ Stammers ]

655
00:30:52,317 --> 00:30:54,017
What the hell
happened to him?

656
00:30:54,786 --> 00:30:57,221
Mmm--
Uh--

657
00:30:57,223 --> 00:31:00,390
Why don't you
just come clean, huh?

658
00:31:00,392 --> 00:31:02,893
I'm gonna find out
the whole truth
about it anyway.

659
00:31:04,462 --> 00:31:06,630
Hank?
Yeah?

660
00:31:06,632 --> 00:31:11,568
You want--
You want your son
to get married, right?

661
00:31:11,570 --> 00:31:12,669
Of course.
Yeah.

662
00:31:12,671 --> 00:31:14,204
Is this guy dead?

663
00:31:16,374 --> 00:31:19,843
[ Stammers ]
And you trust me,
right?

664
00:31:19,845 --> 00:31:21,578
Not particularly.

665
00:31:22,914 --> 00:31:26,183
I had a D.U.I.
when I was 23.
Huge mistake.

666
00:31:26,185 --> 00:31:28,785
Deeply regret it, man.

667
00:31:33,524 --> 00:31:36,493
- Good.
[ Laughs ]
- [ Laughs ]

668
00:31:36,495 --> 00:31:39,363
- I knew all about that.
- Hey!

669
00:31:39,365 --> 00:31:41,732
I was just
giving you a test.
All right!

670
00:31:43,201 --> 00:31:45,736
Now, honey,
chop up this body.

671
00:31:45,738 --> 00:31:48,338
This creepo here, he was--

672
00:31:48,340 --> 00:31:51,408
He was trying to take
this special day...

673
00:31:51,410 --> 00:31:55,112
away from Robbie, you know--

674
00:31:55,114 --> 00:31:56,580
Away from us.

675
00:31:58,216 --> 00:32:01,485
You may be many
not-so-great things,

676
00:32:02,453 --> 00:32:04,888
Hank Fletcher,

677
00:32:04,890 --> 00:32:09,259
but you--
you have always been
a good father.

678
00:32:10,728 --> 00:32:13,030
Robbie--

679
00:32:13,032 --> 00:32:15,198
[ Whispers ]
Robbie needs his daddy
right now.

680
00:32:15,934 --> 00:32:18,201
[ Exhales ]

681
00:32:18,203 --> 00:32:19,736
How small
you want the pieces?

682
00:32:19,738 --> 00:32:23,640
Oh, probably
like 10 total.

683
00:32:23,642 --> 00:32:26,376
I've never
done this before.

684
00:32:26,378 --> 00:32:28,378
I'll start with the legs
and work my way up.

685
00:32:28,380 --> 00:32:30,714
- We shouldn't be doing this.
- Oh, hush, Ted.

686
00:32:31,616 --> 00:32:33,817
Okay. You, uh--

687
00:32:33,819 --> 00:32:35,585
You-- You do it--

688
00:32:35,587 --> 00:32:37,521
[ Ted ]
Oh, God.
Hank.

689
00:32:38,489 --> 00:32:40,757
You know, for--
for Robbie.

690
00:32:40,759 --> 00:32:41,892
[ Muttering ]

691
00:32:44,595 --> 00:32:46,029
Let me just...

692
00:32:47,398 --> 00:32:49,099
get him ready here.

693
00:32:49,101 --> 00:32:51,034
[ Yvette ]
Okay.
[ Grunting ]

694
00:32:53,438 --> 00:32:54,705
Ooh.

